🚀 EC2 Virtual Machine Creation – Full Steps
🔹 Step 1: Login to AWS
Open: https://aws.amazon.com/
Click Sign In
Login using your AWS account
🔹 Step 2: Open EC2 Dashboard
In search bar → type EC2
Click EC2 Dashboard
🔹 Step 3: Launch Instance
Click Launch Instance
🔹 Step 4: Configure Instance
1. Name
Enter: MyFirstVM
2. Choose OS (AMI)
Select: Amazon Linux 2023
3. Instance Type
Choose: t2.micro / t3.micro (Free tier)
4. Key Pair (IMPORTANT)
Click Create new key pair
Name: my-key
Type: .pem
Download and save safely
5. Network Settings
Allow:
✅ SSH (Port 22)
✅ HTTP (Port 80)
🔹 Step 5: Launch Instance
Click Launch Instance
🔹 Step 6: Check Instance Status
Go to Instances
Verify:
State = Running
Public IP generated
🔹 Step 7: Security Configuration
Open Security Group
Check inbound rule:
Type	Port	Source
SSH	22	0.0.0.0/0
🔹 Step 8: Connect to Instance
Method 1 (Browser – sometimes fails)
Click Connect
Select EC2 Instance Connect
Click Connect
